snippet.textDisplay:
AC, keep up the wonderful videos.
I am another who found your channel through the Fire Nation, and I just want to say that although my personal fear of ants has not abated, your channel is one that I keep coming to. (I was attacked as a child by fire ants in Florida; who knew that they had a back door to their nest?) I still dislike ants, but your channel is a safe haven from which to watch some fascinating animals.
You are teaching many about one of the cleanup crews of Planet Earth, and how they live, eat, reproduce, as well as pass on to be a part of this earth again. You even have some footage and information that even the dedicated etymologists don't. Awesome.
Keep up the good work. I'm so glad you have "resurrected" the Fire Nation/Phoenix [nation]/whatever your new ant colony will be named. (I like Phoenix Nation, myself.)
